{
  "texts": [
    "HVS [94] extends HNSW's base layer by refining the construction of hierarchical layers.",
    "Instead of random selection, nodes are assigned to layers based on local density to better capture data distribution.",
    "Each layer forms a Voronoi diagram and uses multi-level quantization, increasing dimensionality by a factor of 2 in each lower layer.",
    "Search at the base layer is similar to that of HNSW.",
    "LSHAPG [163] combines HNSW graphs with multiple hash tables based on the LSB-Tree structure [133] to enhance search efficiency."
  ]
}